The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, September 17, 2003 				 Arafat adviser urges truce
																								Ramallah, Sept. 16 (Reuters): Yasser Arafats security adviser today urged Israel to accept a truce as the UN Security Council prepared to vote on a resolution opposing Israeli threats to remove the Palestinian President.																								Palestinian and international officials say Israeli action against Arafat could ignite the region and destroy a US-backed peace plan. But the resolution faced a veto by the US which said it failed to condemn Palestinian terrorism. 
